	 <title>Appendix A - File Structures</title> 
	 <para>This appendix outlines the various file formats used in the different
		  components of the Dataphor product.</para> 
	 <sect1 id="DataphorConfigFiles"> 
		  <sect1info> 
				<revhistory> 
					 <revision> 
						  <revnumber>1</revnumber> 
						  <date>May 28, 2002 9:33:09 AM MDT</date> 
						  <revdescription> 
								<para>DXC to DocBook</para> 
						  </revdescription> 
					 </revision> 
				</revhistory> 
				<keywordset> 
					 <keyword>File Extensions</keyword> 
					 <keyword>Configuration files</keyword> 
				</keywordset> 
		  </sect1info> 
		  <title>Dataphor File Structures</title> 
		  <para> The several sample applications contain files which contain
				comments about structure and function. Look at the files in the
				<symbol>ReferenceApplication</symbol>, <symbol>IssueTracker</symbol>, and
				<symbol>Pubs</symbol> for details of structure and function of each file type.
				</para> 
		  <sect2> 
				<title>File Extensions</title> 
				<para> Dataphor uses the following file extensions: 
					 <informaltable> 
						  <tgroup cols="2">
								<colspec colwidth="*" colname="col1" colnum="1"/>
								<colspec colwidth="*" colname="col2" colnum="2"/> 
								<thead> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">File extension</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2">Description</entry> 
									 </row> 
								</thead> 
								<tbody> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.D4</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> 
													 <link role="cref"
													  linkend="DCFDAEScript">Dataphor DAE D4 Script</link> </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.dft</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> 
													 <link role="cref"
													  linkend="DCFFrontendTheme">Dataphor Frontend Theme</link> </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.dfs</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> 
													 <link role="cref"
													  linkend="DCFFrontendSession">Dataphor Frontend Session</link> </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.d4c</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> 
													 <link role="cref"
													  linkend="DCFCatalogFormat">Dataphor DAE Catalog</link> </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.config</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> 
													 <link role="cref"
													  linkend="DCFConfigFormat">Configuration File</link> </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.dnt</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> 
													 <link role="cref"
													  linkend="DCFNodeTypesDnt">Dataphor Frontend Node Type Table</link> </para>
												</entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.dfi</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> Used by the windows client cache and
													 the default customization engine to store surrogate mappings to files. The
													 files are all named unique identifiers, while the "mapping" from a longer
													 string key to the file names is contained in this index file. </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.dfc</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> Dataphor Frontend client cache data
													 file. </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.dil</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> Dataphor Interface Language file.
													 </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
									 <row> 
										  <entry colname="col1">.dilx</entry> 
										  <entry colname="col2"> 
												<para> Dataphor Interface Language eXtended
													 file. </para> </entry> 
									 </row> 
								</tbody> 
						  </tgroup> 
					 </informaltable> </para> 
		  </sect2> 
		  <sect2 id="DUGDAEServerServicesFiles"> 
				<sect2info> 
					 <revhistory> 
						  <revision> 
								<revnumber>1</revnumber> 
								<date>May 28, 2002 9:33:09 AM MDT</date> 
								<revdescription> 
									 <para>DXC to DocBook</para> 
								</revdescription> 
						  </revision> 
					 </revhistory> 
				</sect2info> 
				<title>DAE Server Services Files</title> 
				<para>Files used to affect the behavior of the DAE Server
					 Services.</para> 
				<sect3 id="DCFCatalog"> 
					 <sect3info> 
						  <revhistory> 
								<revision> 
									 <revnumber>1</revnumber> 
									 <date>May 28, 2002 9:33:09 AM MDT</date> 
									 <revdescription> 
										  <para>DXC to DocBook</para> 
									 </revdescription> 
								</revision> 
						  </revhistory> 
					 </sect3info> 
					 <title>Catalog</title> 
					 <para>This file is used by the DAE to persist catalog
						  information. When the DAE starts, it restores catalog from this file.</para> 
					 <para>Located in the "user's" directory.</para> 
				</sect3> 
				<sect3 id="DCFDaeServiceConfig"> 
					 <sect3info> 
						  <revhistory> 
								<revision> 
									 <revnumber>1</revnumber> 
									 <date>May 28, 2002 9:33:09 AM MDT</date> 
									 <revdescription> 
										  <para>DXC to DocBook</para> 
									 </revdescription> 
								</revision> 
						  </revhistory> 
					 </sect3info> 
					 <title>DAE Service Config</title> 
					 <para>Settings which affect the behavior of the DAE
						  Service.</para> 
					 <sect4> 
						  <title>Settings</title> 
						  <para>Located in the "all users" directory.</para> 
					 </sect4> 
					 <sect4> 
						  <title>See Also</title> 
						  <para> 
								<link role="cref" linkend="DCFConfigFormat">Config File
									 Format</link> </para> 
					 </sect4> 
				</sect3> 
		  </sect2> 
