				<sect3 id="DCFCatalogFormat"> 
					 <sect3info> 
						  <revhistory> 
								<revision> 
									 <revnumber>1</revnumber> 
									 <date>May 28, 2002 9:33:09 AM MDT</date> 
									 <revdescription> 
										  <para>DXC to DocBook</para> 
									 </revdescription> 
								</revision> 
						  </revhistory> 
					 </sect3info> 
					 <title>Catalog Format</title> 
					 <para> Contains a BOP persisted serialization of a DAE catalog.
						  </para> 
					 <para> This contains the complete "data dictionary" for the DAE
						  server. This is loaded when a DAE Server is started, and saved when the DAE
						  Server is stopped. This file can also be manually saved and loaded with the
						  SaveCatalog() and LoadCatalog() commands. </para> 
				</sect3> 
				<sect3 id="DCFConfigFormat"> 
					 <sect3info> 
						  <revhistory> 
								<revision> 
									 <revnumber>1</revnumber> 
									 <date>May 28, 2002 9:33:09 AM MDT</date> 
									 <revdescription> 
										  <para>DXC to DocBook</para> 
									 </revdescription> 
								</revision> 
						  </revhistory> 
					 </sect3info> 
					 <title>Configuration Format</title> 
					 <para> Dataphor configuration files have XML-formatted content.
						  There are two elements defined: a <symbol>settingscontainer</symbol> which
						  contains one or more <symbol>settingsitem</symbol>s. </para> 
					 <sect4> 
						  <title>Elements</title> 
						  <para> 
								<informaltable> 
									 <tgroup cols="2">
										  <colspec colwidth="*" colname="col1" colnum="1"/>
										  <colspec colwidth="*" colname="col2" colnum="2"/> 
										  <thead> 
												<row> 
													 <entry colname="col1">Element
														  Name</entry> 
													 <entry
													 colname="col2">Description</entry> 
												</row> 
										  </thead> 
										  <tbody> 
												<row> 
													 <entry
													 colname="col1">settingscontainer</entry> 
													 <entry colname="col2"> 
														  <para> Contains one or more
																<symbol>settingsitem</symbol>s. </para> 
														  <para> See the example for special
																name spaces that must be defined. </para> </entry> 
												</row> 
												<row> 
													 <entry
													 colname="col1">settingsitem</entry> 
													 <entry colname="col2"> 
														  <para> Provides a place to store
																name/value pairs in the configuration file. </para> 
														  <para> The <symbol>name</symbol>
																attribute stores the name for the name/value pair of the settings item. </para>
														  
														  <para> The <symbol>value</symbol>
																attribute stores the value for the name/value pair of the settings item.
																</para> </entry> 
												</row> 
										  </tbody> 
									 </tgroup> 
								</informaltable> </para> 
					 </sect4> 
					 <sect4> 
						  <title>Remarks</title> 
						  <para> Applications may maintain configuration files using
								the settings API of Dataphor BOP. This API makes a configuration file appear
								like the Windows registry. </para> 
					 </sect4> 
					 <sect4> 
						  <title>Example</title> 
						  <para> 
								<programlisting> &lt;settingscontainer xmlns:bop="www.alphora.com/schemas/bop"
	xmlns="Alphora.Dataphor.BOP,Alphora.Dataphor.BOP"&gt;
	&lt;settingsitem name="SessionURI" 
		value="http://localhost/environment/BugTracker/main.dfs" /&gt;
&lt;/settingscontainer&gt; </programlisting> </para> 
					 </sect4> 
				</sect3> 
		  </sect2> 
	 </sect1> 
